rComments: Great feedback. I felt like my writing improved by following his commentary.

What a wonderful, sincere, incredible person. Probably one of the best teachers I've ever had in my life, not just at UofT (and this is not hyperbole). His classes are always worthwhile, well-planned, intelligently delivered, and even uproariously funny at times, and he is always upfront about everything. I'd give anything to have him again.

Hands down one of the greatest professors I've had at UofT - and I'm a psych specialist. He's hilarious but knows his stuff inside and out. He's also extremely honest, which is so nice to see. He'll tell you he may disagree, but you don't get the feeling he's belittling you in any way. Hard marker for sure, but lots of feedback to improve. Love him

The material is extremely intellectually stimulating and the classes are discussion-based. He genuinely cares about his students and he is hilarious! One of the best English classes I have taken in my four years :)

Professor Gang is refreshing after encountering several professors that are condescending. He is young, approachable, funny and always replies to emails and made the time to see me outside of office hours. I truly appreciate his understanding and his fantastic communication. Really enjoyed the way he motivated everyone to participate. My favourite.
Hard material and even harder marking schemes. Still, he's a great guy who really knows his stuff.
